Karlene /kar-lene/ [2 sylls.] as a girls' name is of Old German, Latin and English origin, and the name Karlene means free man. Karlene is a version of Carlene (Old German). Karlene is also a variation of Carly (Latin). Karlene is also used as a derivative of Caroline (Old German), Charlotte (Old German), Karleen (English) and Karolina (Slavic, Old German).
